The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Sunday, July 11, 2004  Corporate Briefs																								 IT company Birlasoft will ramp up its India operations and increase its headcount by 400 by August. quot;There has been a significant increase in our offshore work. Birlasofts continuous expansion in the IT sector has led to an increased requirement for software professionals, quot; COO Kamal Manshara mani said. The New Jersey-based company had earlier announced its plan to recruit about 850 software professionals by March 2005. 																								 ICICI Bank and Punjab amp; Sind Bank has launched the Punjab amp; Sind Bank-ICICI Bank credit card, available in three variants 																								d blue. This marks ICICI Banks first public sector bank partnership in the credit card business.																								 Icra has upgraded the performance ratings of the West Bengal State Electricity Board (WBSEB), indicating the boards improved level of efficiency. WBSEB had been ranked 11th at the all-India level, overtaking other states like Tamil Nadu and Maharashtra, a release issued by the board said. 																								 IBM India has announced the availability of a secure virtual private network for independent software vendors (ISVs) and business partners to provide remote countrywide access to its IBM Innovation Centre for Business Partners. The new service will enable ISVs and business partners to utilise the IBM centre remotely, by reducing costs and enhancing software development, an IBM statement said.																								 SBI Life Insurance Company, a joint venture between State Bank of India and Cardiff SA of France, has launched the SBI Life money back plan. We have designed this product keeping in mind the needs of our customers and we hope that they will find this product interesting and useful, SBI Life CEO and MD S. Krishnamurthy said.																								 Simpay, a mobile commerce company, has selected Tata Infotech for testing the commercial rollout of its mobile payment scheme scheduled for launch early next year. Tata infotech will support Simpay in testing the central processing systems and the readiness of Simpays members for scheme launch, quot; a company statement said.																								 Allahabad Bank has gone live on Real Time Gross Settlement (RTGS), which would enable the bank to settle transfer of funds and inter-bank transactions online at a real time. This would also reduce the risks in payment systems, Chairman and managing director O. N. Singh said.																								 Gontermann Piepers (India) Ltd (GPI), a member of Ispat Group of Companies, will organise a ceremony to kick off total productive maintenance methods on July 7 at Pailan. Yoshio Egami, a consultant from Japan Institute of Plant Maintenance will inaugurate the function. ADVERTISEMENT
